It has a clean car fax. Formerly owned by ZZ Top drummer Frank Beard.Please feel free to call with any questions.  775-843-2549 for David or James 775-720-8356.

Porsche and the 911 make history every year with the ongoing model that has remained in its same basic form since day one as well as retaining the same model name since 1966.  Porsche has never tried to reinvent the car, just make it better and more enticing to the buyers.

This custom built 911 is done extremely well and was started with a 1972 long nose body and being tastefully converted into a turbo wide body look.  All body panels were sourced from Porsche and the front end retained the long nose structure internally to be easily converted back to its original look.  Rear turbo flares are butt-welded like the original 930's and carry the slant body gills.  The 3.0L engine has been slightly modified and carry PMO 46mm carbs and intakes.  B&B style stainless exhaust with Bursch mufflers are installed nicely and the MSD ignition allows the car to fire up quickly and easily.  Transmission is the 915 5speed manual and has about 3k miles on the rebuild.  Front are rear suspension have been modified with Weltmeister 19mm sway bar kit and triangulate strut races.  Wilwood superlite II calipers with 3.5 bolt spacing to accommodate the massive 19in GT3 Porsche wheels.  Front bonnet houses a new 18-gallon fuel cell that sits in a steel cradle aand a 12v electric pump in the smugglers box.  Interior has fresh dash pad, proper working gauges and new Procar black leather sport seats along with RS door panels and hardware.

This is a very unique and professionally built 911 that is ready for any adventure you choose to pursue.  If you want to track it, race it or just enjoy it, there is nothing better than to buy one already done with all the big ticket items already paid for by someone else.  The cost to duplicate a car like this would cost $30k to just get a starting point.

The car quickly comes a live and with a short warm up period this 911 is ready for the road and the sound that it produces is a quite intoxicating and hard to resist.  Buy a car that will get you noticed at the next Porsche club meet or car show.  Surely you will not be missed.

Professionally restored in 2012. A 1986 911 cabriolet with a 959 body kit, black exterior with a black top, & black interior. Sweet little car. Come take a look.
If you are in the market for a 930 Turbo, but don't have a cool $100k+ to drop on a classic car, then you need to take a closer look at this '75 Porsche 930 replica.

The beneficiary of a 930 Metal wide-body kit with fiberglass slant nose fenders and a built 3.0L six-cylinder with less than 5000 miles on the engine, transmission and clutch! This Porsche is ready for your local track day or a night out on the town. It's not perfect by any means, but its a car that you can drive and enjoy today! Make no mistake, this motor cruises so well on the highway at 70mph, but downshift to pass a car and you'll see that this 3.0L loves that 4,000 - 8,000 RPM range. The motor changes pitch, and will absolutely shove you back in the seat when overtaking a car in front of you. It's one of the most fun classic Porsches I have ever driven.
Don't miss out on this great opportunity!

Offered here is a clean and tastefully modified 1986 Porsche 911 Cabriolet for consideration. The car is painted in the original Guards Red paint over a black interior and new black soft top. This car came to Michigan ten years ago out of Boca Raton, FL with 65k on the odometer and a folder full of service records from Edge Automotive, Inc. In 2012, our client brought the car to Euro Autowerks, one the best in the Porsche business, for a full $18k plus engine rebuild. The motor was then upgraded with larger cylinders to go from a 3.2L to a 3.4L with new and bigger pistons and refurbished crankshaft. Transmission and clutch done as well. A custom dual exhaust system and chrome Fuch wheels are also nice finishing touches. Since 2008, over $22k has been spent has been spent at Euro Autowerks to dial this Cab in. All receipts and service records available. Be sure to check out the video as well. This is an awesome looking and driving classic 911 convertible at a reasonable price considering all the work that's been done. Call or e-mail if interested, or to make an offer. Thank you for looking.

1986 Porsche 911 Carrera Cabriola Coupe Convertible, manual 5 speed, a/c, no known Accidents, not driven in rain or snow. Two owners.

Carpets and headliner: good condition. The engine bay: good order; trunk is tidy with tools and a spare tire. Good factory alloy “Fuchs” wheels with minor scrapes fitted with 215/60 R15 Yokohama Avid H4S tires.
Indicated Mileage: 70,363

As its name indicated, this second-generation Carrera featured a larger 3.2-liter engine with fuel injection controlled by a digital motor electronics (DME) system. This combination produced 231-hp.  A slightly different 3.2 version was developed for the American and Japanese markets with lower compression, rated at 207-hp, in order to meet stricter emissions standards and operate on unleaded fuel. The 1986 Carrera dash was redesigned with larger air vents.

This 1986 Porsche 911 Carrera Cabriolet; one of 19,987 full convertibles built between 1984 and 1986. It is a standard narrow-body 911 and a U.S. market car, thus, it is equipped with catalytic converters which somewhat limits the car's performance. Top speed was 124-mph while acceleration from 0 to 60 took 7.0 seconds. Original options on the car included metallic gold paint, leather interior, and a cassette player.

This car was sold new to Dr. Paul Corso from Heishman Porsche/Audi in Arlington, Virginia. He took delivery of the car on May 24, 1986 and, according to the log book still with the car, had it serviced at the dealership until 1989. In April of 2003, it was purchased by Mr. Donald Edward Lucas of Fairfax, Virginia with 60,598 miles on the odometer and was serviced by Craftsman Automotive owned by Alan Himes in Sterling, VA.

sleigh.  Classic 1984 Porsche 911 Targa in Guards red with black interior.  The vehicle is adult owned, with 132K, non-smoking, garaged miles, and has spent its life in Texas, with no known rust, a clean CarFax report, and a dash with no warping or cracks.

Current  owner purchased the vehicle in April 2012. Life circumstances are forcing sale. The vehicle has received regular maintenance and has always been garage kept; it has been a weekend driver for the last 5 years with less than 20K miles during that time. The vehicle was recently (Sept 2017) serviced at Oswalt's in Mesquite with an oil change and A/C service. A full inspection of the car was done at the time, see below for details.

At the time the vehicle was serviced there are two items noted that will need to be addressed by the new owner.  First is a rough shift between 1st and 2nd the mechanic says will require opening the transmission to diagnose and repair.  Second is a very minor oil leak.  The vehicle does not leave puddles on the garage floor nor does the engine smoke.
CarFax report shows 35 entries with 0 accidents and 5 service records.  Most entries are for title transfers.  There are no known wrecks or rust.  The vehicle has been in Texas all its life.

Vehicle has working A/C, power windows, powerbrakes, and aftermarket Pioneer radio/cd player. Tires are in good shape and show even wear with back tires new within the past 2 years. There are a few minor blemishes we have attempted to show in the photos, but none over a quarter in size.  Paint still shows well.

Interior in good condition for its age and wasn't used as a kennel or pet transport.  There is one seam on passenger seat requiring attention and wear on the bolster for driver's seat.  Additionally the driver's door panel is cracked but may be salvagable.  Dash looks like the day it came from the showroom.
